id: jf-59hr
title: Honor output formats and survive Playback Reporting user-list failures
description: "All usage-stats subcommands hard-coded Toon despite advertised global/local formats, and the installed Playback Reporting plugin returns HTTP 500 for user_usage_stats/user_list. Route every report through the shared formatter and fall back read-only to core Jellyfin users with explicit per-record provenance when only the optional plugin user-list endpoint fails."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: formatting,plugin,resilience,usage-stats
created_at: "2026-07-21T19:13:37.700Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T20:03:29.873Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T20:03:29.044Z"
author: codex-jellyfin
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "All usage-stats commands honor Toon, JSON, YAML, Markdown, Table, and Raw format selection; A plugin user-list HTTP 500 falls back to GET /Users and marks unknown plugin membership explicitly; Other plugin errors remain structured failures; Unit and compiled-binary live E2E tests pass without mutations"
goal: jf-mqpo
value: Keep optional plugin diagnostics useful and machine-readable on imperfect installations.
impact: Removes a live E2E failure and a cross-format contract violation.
outcome: Consistent structured usage reports with a transparent safe fallback.
why_now: The mandatory live suite produced 176 passes and one failure at the plugin user-list endpoint.
parent: jf-gn5j
reviewer: maintainer
risk: high
confidence: high
sprint: jellyfin-10.11.11
severity: high
environment: Jellyfin 10.11.11 with Playback Reporting plugin; jf-cli compiled binary
repro_steps: Run JELLYFIN_READ_ONLY=1 jf-cli usage-stats users; observe plugin HTTP 500. Run with --format json and observe hard-coded Toon before the fix.
resolution: Every usage-stats command uses the shared formatter; only plugin user-list HTTP 500 falls back to core users with explicit provenance and unknown membership.
expected_result: All advertised formats remain parseable and optional plugin failure does not break safe user reporting.
actual_result: "Focused tests pass and the compiled read-only Jellyfin acceptance suite passes all 177 cases, including usage-stats users and movies."
component: usage-stats
customer_impact: Agent pipelines fail or receive the wrong serialization format.
